  "prompt": "What are the names of the specific executives at Marvel and Fox that are preventing X-Men & Fantastic Four characters from appearing in the Marvel Cinematic Universe?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff date in October 2023, there haven't been specific executives at Marvel or Fox publicly named as preventing the X-Men and Fantastic Four characters from appearing in the Marvel Cinematic Universe. Instead, the issue largely stemmed from legal and business complexities. For many years, Fox held the film rights to the X-Men and Fantastic Four franchises, preventing Marvel Studios from incorporating those characters into the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU).\n\nHowever, these issues began to resolve following Disney's acquisition of 21st Century Fox in 2019. This acquisition included the transfer of film rights for the X-Men and Fantastic Four to Disney, which owns Marvel Studios. Following the acquisition, Marvel Studios has begun planning to integrate these characters into future MCU projects.\n\nWhile specific executives might have been involved in negotiations or decisions during this period, information about individual decision-makers wasn\u2019t widely publicized, and the focus was more on the outcomes of corporate agreements and restructuring. Therefore, I can't provide specific names of individuals who were responsible for the situation, but it was mainly a result of film rights and corporate acquisitions.",
